explanation:
No controlling expression in the provided function is statically invariant. The only control statement is the if condition:

if (!device->name || !strlen(device->name) || device->num_regions > METAL_MAX_DEVICE_REGIONS)

Each subexpression depends on runtime data: device->name (pointer value), the length of the string it points to (runtime content), and device->num_regions (runtime numeric value) compared to the compile-time constant METAL_MAX_DEVICE_REGIONS. None of these are compile-time constants or otherwise guaranteed to be invariant. There are no loops or other conditional constructs in the function that could form an invariant controlling expression (no infinite loops or do-while constructs). Also, the logical-OR uses short-circuit evaluation, so strlen(device->name) is not invoked when device->name is NULL, avoiding undefined behavior. Therefore, no fragments require further investigation under MISRA C 2023 Rule 14.3.
